Remote data

Powers many of the most popular mobile applications

AJAX and XHR

XHR: XMLHttpResponse

AJAX: Asynchronous JavaScript and XHR

Use Titanium's HTTPClient module to pull data from a remote API

var xhr = Ti.Network.createHTTPClient
	onload = function()
	onError = function()

etc

Ti.API.debug(this.stuff)

xhr.open("GET", "URL");
xhr.send();


Ti.Network.
(properties)
NETWORK_LAN
NETWORK_MOBILE
NETWORK_NONE
NETWORK_UNKNOWN
NETWORK_WIFI
networkType
online //needed to check for connectivity

(methods)
addEventListener()
createHTTPClient() //Necessary to access remote data
fireEvent()
getNetworkType()
getOnline()
removeEventListener()

Only has one event: change
Listens for a network change. The more testing for "change" the more taxing on the battery.

HTTPClient will retrieve and/or send data from remote servers

handles a connection with a remote URL to allow data retrieval and manipulation

Methods:
.open()
.send()

Properties

.responseText
.onload
.onerror
.statusText *
.timeout

* Only property not necessary for handling the data and the request itself



EXAMPLE CODE:
var url = "http://dev.markitondemand.com/Api/v2/Lookup/json?input=NFLX";
var xhr = Ti.Network.createHTTPClient({
	onload: function(evt) {
		Ti.API.info("Stock INfo received: " + this.responseText);
	},
	onerror: function(evt) {
		Ti.API.debug("Error: " + evt.error);
	},
	timeout: 5000 // in milliseconds
});

xhr.open("GET", url);
xhr.send();

